@enuinc That's correct, Gdspy presents data in *user units*, not the integers written in the GDSII file.

If you need to change the units when you import a GDSII file (because you are using different *user units* in different files, for example), it's easier to use the `unit` argument in [GdsLibrary.read_gds](http://gdspy.readthedocs.io/en/latest/library.html#gdspy.GdsLibrary.read_gds).

You might also be interested in [this specification](http://boolean.klaasholwerda.nl/interface/bnf/gdsformat.html#rec_units).

