The above is failing looking for the trailing router prompt (i.e. it didn't find the router prompt before the timeout which is set to 8 seconds)

One situation where this would happen is if your config change modified the router hostname (since that changes the router trailing prompt).

Adding the following method to the MergedNamesDict works around this for me:
```
class MergedNamesDict(object):
    # ...(snip)...
    def get(self, value, default):
        return self.dicts.get(value, default=default)
```
It might not be pretty, but it works!

