@ahojnnes After some testing, I believe the implementation in skimage is correct. The difference may lie in the **antialiasing** filtering, which is probably mandatory in Pillow and optional in MATLAB.

the snippets are as follows.

First, I generated scaled down versions of `astronaut` using Pillow and skimage.

~~~python
image = astronaut()
image_processed_1 = Image.fromarray(astronaut())
image_processed_1 = image_processed_1.resize((128, 128), resample=Image.BICUBIC)
image_processed_2 = rescale(image, 0.25, order=3, mode='nearest')
imsave('astronaut.png',image)
imsave('astronaut_PIL.png',image_processed_1)
imsave('astronaut_skimage.png',img_as_ubyte(image_processed_2))
~~~

Then I downloaded the three saved `png` files and ran the following MATLAB script to do resizing in MATLAB and compare the images produced.

~~~matlab
im = imread('astronaut.png');
im_rescaled_aa = double(imresize(im, 0.25, 'bicubic'));
im_rescaled_noaa = double(imresize(im, 0.25, 'bicubic', 'Antialiasing', false));

im_pil = double(imread('astronaut_PIL.png'));
im_skimage = double(imread('astronaut_skimage.png'));

diff_aa_pil = im_pil(:)-im_rescaled_aa(:);
diff_aa_skimage = im_skimage(:)-im_rescaled_aa(:);
diff_noaa_skimage = im_skimage(:)-im_rescaled_noaa(:);

fprintf('diff mean between matlab aa and pil: %f, std: %f\n', mean(diff_aa_pil), std(diff_aa_pil));
fprintf('diff mean between matlab aa and skimage: %f, std: %f\n', mean(diff_aa_skimage), std(diff_aa_skimage));
fprintf('diff mean between matlab no aa and skimage: %f, std: %f\n', mean(diff_noaa_skimage), std(diff_noaa_skimage));
~~~

and I get the following result.

~~~
>> output_matlab_version
diff mean between matlab aa and pil: 0.001567, std: 0.485866
diff mean between matlab aa and skimage: 0.007202, std: 9.993774
diff mean between matlab no aa and skimage: -0.063883, std: 0.426613
~~~

Since these images are saved in lossy `unit8`, and the difference between matlab no aa and skimage is so close, I believe the implementation is correct and they differ in some minor details.

But I have two questions in general.

